in star formation for\nspirals. The threshold and the efficiency of star formation play a very\nimportant role in the chemical evolution of spiral disks and an efficiency\nvarying with radius can be used to regulate the star formation. The oxygen\nabundance gradient can steepen or flatten in time depending on the choice of\nthis parameter\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 23 Apr 2010 14:14:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-18"}
